(Analysis) Tj
0 -12 Td
(--------) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Threads outperform processes at higher worker counts due to:) Tj
0 -12 Td
(1. No JVM startup overhead per worker) Tj
0 -12 Td
(2. No pipe serialization \(processes send all points via stdin\)) Tj
0 -12 Td
(3. Direct shared memory access vs IPC) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(At low worker counts \(1-2\), overhead differences are minimal.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(At higher counts \(8+\), threads show 30-45% improvement.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(Processes degrade at high worker counts \(e.g. 32 processes = 13.3s vs 4.5s) Tj
0 -12 Td
(for threads on 5000 points\) due to cumulative JVM startup and pipe overhead.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Threads remain flat because shared memory has no per-worker IPC cost.) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
0 -12 Td
(Optimal configuration: 8 threads \(matches CPU logical cores, best performance\)) Tj
0 -12 Td
() Tj
